  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">All session-files-index queries MUST apply both `tenantId eq '...'` AND `sessionId eq '...'` filters — the OData clause is appended via `BuildSearchOptions` and ANDed with the existing tenant filter so tenant isolation is preserved.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All R5 AI capabilities live in BFF; this task does NOT alter that — `RagService` stays in `Sprk.Bff.Api` per ADR-013 Zone A.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — zero new top-level `Program.cs` lines. If any new registration is needed (none expected; the index-name config is already covered by extending `AiSearchOptions`), it goes inside `Infrastructure/DI/AnalysisServicesModule.cs` per the feature-module pattern.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces ZERO new feature flags. `SessionId` is an optional parameter on the existing options record — NOT a kill-switch boundary. ADR-032 Null-Object pattern is NOT applicable to this change (the existing `NullRagService` kill-switch already covers `RagService` as a whole when `Analysis:Enabled` is false; the new `SessionId` parameter inherits that coverage without any new wiring).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — per-task verification mandatory. Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline. R5 budget ≤ +1 MB single-task delta; this task ≤ +0.1 MB target (additive property + small routing branch). Hard ceiling 60 MB compressed (current baseline ~45.65 MB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 (reuse mandate)">MUST extend the EXISTING `RagSearchOptions` record + EXISTING `RagService` class — MUST NOT introduce parallel `SessionRagSearchOptions` / `SessionRagService` / new search service. Cite this rule in the PR description.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (no new flags)">Zero new feature flags introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3 (DI discipline)">If a new service registration is required (none expected), it goes inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` — zero new lines in `Program.cs`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 (publish-size)">Per-task `dotnet publish` measurement reported in task notes / PR description (absolute + delta).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7 (test obligation)">Modifying `Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs` triggers the test obligation — new tests MUST land in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/RagServiceTests.cs` (extend existing) covering both routing branches.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-09">General grounded Q&amp;A over session-scoped files routes through `RagSearchOptions.sessionId` filter; this task ships the filter primitive that downstream tasks depend on.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-10 (back-compat)">New `SessionId` parameter is ADDITIVE. Existing callers (R3/R4 wizard `streamSummarize`, knowledge-base admin, document-classifier handler, AI analysis nodes) MUST behave identically when they pass no `SessionId`. Verified via existing test suite remaining green.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec PR-02">Per-task BFF publish-size verification — report in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">BFF additions governance — this task modifies `Services/Ai/`; cite Placement Justification in PR description (placement: BFF; criterion: existing service extension, not net-new capability).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">The session-files index name MUST be admin-overridable via `AiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName` (default `"spaarke-session-files"`), mirroring the existing `KnowledgeIndexName` / `RagReferencesIndexName` / `FilesIndexName` properties.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Routing decision uses `SearchIndexClient.GetSearchClient(indexName)` directly when `SessionId` is provided (NOT `IKnowledgeDeploymentService.GetSearchClientAsync`) — session-files is a shared session-scoped index per task 001 routing decision; deployment-service routing is for tenant-dedicated knowledge indexes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">When `SessionId` is provided, the `KnowledgeSourceId(s)` / `ExcludeKnowledgeSourceIds` / `ParentEntityType+Id` filters are NOT applicable to session-files docs (session-files have `tenantId` + `sessionId` + chunk schema only, no knowledge-source / parent-entity columns). Validate inputs OR silently ignore those filters with a debug log; document the choice in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Privilege-group filter (AIPU2-027) — session-files documents do NOT carry `privilege_group_ids`. Confirm behavior of `PrivilegeFilterBuilder.BuildFilter([])` over a session-files schema during implementation; if it conflicts, branch the privilege filter to a session-files-aware no-op for session-scoped queries (document the decision).</constraint>
  </constraints>

