    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Additive record property on RagSearchOptions" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IRagService.cs (line ~199)">
        `RagSearchOptions` is a C# `record` with `init`-only properties. Add `SessionId`
        as a `public string? SessionId { get; init; }` adjacent to the existing
        `KnowledgeSourceId` (or `ParentEntityId`) initializer. XML-doc the property to
        explain that, when set, search routes to the session-files index and applies a
        `sessionId eq '...'` filter ANDed with the existing `tenantId` filter.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Index-name configuration extension" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Options/AiSearchOptions.cs">
        Add `public string SessionFilesIndexName { get; init; } = "spaarke-session-files";`
        adjacent to the existing `FilesIndexName` / `InsightsIndexName` properties. This
        gives ops the same admin-override knob R2 / R3 use for other indexes.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Session-files routing branch inside SearchAsync" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs (Step 2 of SearchAsync, line ~189)">
        Today: `searchClient = options.DeploymentId.HasValue ? GetSearchClientByDeploymentAsync(...)
        : _deploymentService.GetSearchClientAsync(tenantId, ct);`. Add a precedence branch:
        if `!string.IsNullOrEmpty(options.SessionId)` → use
        `_searchIndexClient.GetSearchClient(_aiSearchOptions.SessionFilesIndexName)`
        (existing injected `SearchIndexClient`). Otherwise fall through to existing
        deployment-routing path. Branch order: SessionId first, then DeploymentId, then
        default tenant routing — most specific first.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Session-files filter clause inside BuildSearchOptions" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs (BuildSearchOptions, line ~935)">
        The existing tenant filter (`filters.Add($"tenantId eq '{EscapeFilterValue(options.TenantId)}'");`)
        is unconditional. ADD: if `!string.IsNullOrEmpty(options.SessionId)` then append
        `filters.Add($"sessionId eq '{EscapeFilterValue(options.SessionId)}'");`. The clause
        joins via " and " (existing pattern). The privilege-group / tags / entity-scope
        filters are gated on session-scoped queries per the constraint above — implement a
        small branch that SKIPS privilege-group filter when `SessionId` is set, since
        session-files docs do not carry that column.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="NullRagService kill-switch coverage" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/NullRagService.cs">
        `NullRagService.SearchAsync` returns an empty `RagSearchResponse` when the kill
        switch is on. The `SessionId` extension inherits this — no separate
        `NullRagService` change is needed. Verify by reading `NullRagService` and noting in
        task notes that the existing throw-FeatureDisabledException / empty-response
        pattern still covers the session-scoped code path with zero new wiring.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Test extension pattern" location="tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/RagServiceTests.cs">
        Extend the existing `RagServiceTests` class with new tests: (a)
        `SearchAsync_WhenSessionIdAbsent_RoutesToTenantKnowledgeIndex`; (b)
        `SearchAsync_WhenSessionIdProvided_RoutesToSessionFilesIndex`; (c)
        `SearchAsync_WhenSessionIdProvided_AppliesTenantAndSessionFilter`; (d)
        `SearchAsync_WhenSessionIdProvided_DoesNotApplyKnowledgeSourceFilter`.
        Use the existing test fixtures' mocked `SearchIndexClient` /
        `IKnowledgeDeploymentService` patterns.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice. The R5 chat agent
      grounds responses on session-uploaded files via session-scoped retrieval against the
      new `spaarke-session-files` Azure AI Search index (provisioned by task 001). This
      task extends the existing `RagService` retrieval primitive — the same service used
      by the existing knowledge-base-grounded wizard path, document-classifier handler, AI
      analysis nodes, and Insights `IndexRetrieveNode` — with an additive `SessionId`
      filter. When R5 downstream tasks (Phase 2 endpoint, Phase 2 LLM tool, Phase 2 chat
      Q&amp;A flow) need to scope retrieval to a chat session's files, they pass
      `options with { SessionId = chatSession.Id }`. Existing callers continue to pass
      no `SessionId` and get the customer-corpus knowledge index they already use.

      Why additive on `RagSearchOptions` and NOT a parallel options class: per R5 CLAUDE.md
      §3.1 reuse mandate (and consistent with how the Insights team extended
      `RagSearchOptions` with subject / artifactType / predicate filters during Wave D),
      `RagSearchOptions` IS the canonical RAG search query DTO. A parallel
      `SessionRagSearchOptions` would diverge and require parallel `RagService` overloads
      that drift. Single record, single service, additive property — back-compat
      preserved by null-default + branch on presence.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">
        Provisions `spaarke-session-files` index on Spaarke Dev. Required for end-to-end
        smoke testing of this task's session-routing branch. NOT required for authoring
        the code change or running unit tests (which mock the SearchClient). Implementer
        can ship the code change against the schema spec in task 001 even if task 001 has
        not yet completed deployment; smoke test against the empty index happens once
        task 001 lands.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 001 (D1-01) provisions the `spaarke-session-files` index whose schema this
        task's routing branch queries. The index includes `tenantId` + `sessionId` fields
        per ADR-014.</item>
      <item>Task 003 (D1-03) parameterizes `RagIndexingPipeline` to WRITE to the session-files
        index. Tasks 002 (this) + 003 are independent and parallel-safe within wave P1-G2:
        002 touches READ-path (`RagService.SearchAsync` + `RagSearchOptions`); 003 touches
        WRITE-path (`RagIndexingPipeline`).</item>
      <item>Insights r2 Wave D added `subject` / `artifactType` / `predicate` filters to
        `RagSearchOptions` — the same additive-extension pattern this task uses. Reference
        `notes/insights-r2-coordination.md` to verify no merge conflict in the property
        ordering.</item>
      <item>Task 007 (D1-07) consumes the session-scoped retrieval indirectly via the
        cleanup `IHostedService`. Task 009 (D1-09) extends Phase 1 tests covering this
        task's branches end-to-end.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

